P3.14: Startup Error Handling Fix

Problem:
If server startup failed (e.g., ListenAndServe returned error) after
background services had started, those services were left running.

Solution:
1. Added 'defer shutdown()' at line 229 to ensure cleanup on any exit
2. Wrapped shutdown logic in sync.Once for idempotency (line 202)
3. Shutdown can now be called safely from multiple paths without issues

Key Design Decision:
Using sync.Once instead of removing explicit shutdown() calls from
signal handlers preserves the existing clean separation of concerns.
The signal handler path can still do additional HTTP server shutdown
logic while relying on defer for the basic service cleanup.

Files Modified:
- cmd/agent-deploy/main.go: Added sync import, sync.Once, defer shutdown()
